Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the deployment process for the Modern Data Architecture system:

```plantuml
@startuml mebaysan_Modern-Data-Architecture

actor User
participant "Docker Compose" as DockerCompose
participant "Airbyte Container" as Airbyte
participant "PostgreSQL Container" as PostgreSQL
participant "DBT Container" as DBT
participant "Superset Container" as Superset
participant "Nginx Container" as Nginx

User -> DockerCompose : Start deployment
activate DockerCompose

DockerCompose -> PostgreSQL : Deploy and start
activate PostgreSQL
DockerCompose <-- PostgreSQL : Started

DockerCompose -> Airbyte : Deploy and start
activate Airbyte
DockerCompose <-- Airbyte : Started

DockerCompose -> DBT : Deploy and start
activate DBT
DockerCompose <-- DBT : Started

DockerCompose -> Superset : Deploy and start
activate Superset
DockerCompose <-- Superset : Started

DockerCompose -> Nginx : Deploy and start
activate Nginx
DockerCompose <-- Nginx : Started

User <-- DockerCompose : Deployment complete

Airbyte -> PostgreSQL : Extract and load data
PostgreSQL --> Airbyte : Data loaded

DBT -> PostgreSQL : Transform data
PostgreSQL --> DBT : Data transformed

Superset -> PostgreSQL : Query data
PostgreSQL --> Superset : Return query results

User -> Nginx : Access Superset dashboard
Nginx -> Superset : Proxy request
Superset --> Nginx : Return dashboard
Nginx --> User : Display dashboard

@enduml
```